    <item>
      <title>About Us</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/about.html</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2024 15:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/about.html</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The University of New Haven’s cybersecurity club, cyber@CIT, is a student ran organization dedicated sharing knowledge related to cybersecurity. The club meets weekly to allow students to engage in the practical application of cybersecurity concepts.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;leadership-history&#34;&gt;Leadership History&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;presidents&#34;&gt;Presidents&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Jonathan Chute (2023-Present)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Charles Barone (2021-2023)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Samuel Zurowski (2018-2021)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;TJ Balon (2016-2018)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;James Herbert (2015-2016)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;advisors&#34;&gt;Advisors&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Murat Gunestas (2024-present)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Mark Morton (2023-2024)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Resources</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/resources.html</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2024 15:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/resources.html</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;for-beginners&#34;&gt;For beginners:&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://tryhackme.com/&#34;&gt;TryHackMe&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; cybersecurity platform focused on guided learning&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://overthewire.org/wargames/&#34;&gt;OverTheWire&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; linear-style challenges in different areas&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;red-team&#34;&gt;Red Team&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.hackthebox.com/&#34;&gt;HackTheBox&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; cloud-hosted vulnerable machines to hack&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.vulnhub.com/&#34;&gt;VulnHub&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; vulnerable machines for self-hosting on VirtualBox or VMWare&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.offensive-security.com/labs/&#34;&gt;OffSec Proving Grounds&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; three hours free per day of pentesting labs (or pay)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;blue-team&#34;&gt;Blue Team&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://letsdefend.io/&#34;&gt;LetsDefend&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; blue team training&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;ctfs&#34;&gt;CTFs&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://picoctf.org/&#34;&gt;PicoCTF&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; retired CTF challenges in every common CTF category&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pwn.college/&#34;&gt;pwn.college&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; learning platform focused on binary exploitation&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://ctf101.org/&#34;&gt;CTF Handbook&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; Wiki for CTFs&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;programming&#34;&gt;Programming&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.codecademy.com&#34;&gt;CodeAcademy&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; tons of programming languages to learn on their website&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://realpython.com/&#34;&gt;RealPython&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; various tutorials on Python&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;virtualization&#34;&gt;Virtualization&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.kali.org/&#34;&gt;Kali Linux&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; Linux distro with hacking tools pre-loaded.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.virtualbox.org/&#34;&gt;VirtualBox&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.vmware.com/products/desktop-hypervisor/workstation-and-fusion&#34;&gt;VMWare Workstation&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; VM hypervisors&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.charlesbar.one/unh/ISOs/&#34;&gt;Charles ISO Mirror&lt;/a&gt; &amp;mdash; ISO Mirrors for various machines that could be used.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
